      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Medium close-up shot in an oval frame, depicting a man in urban clothes. Verso: hand-written dedication in Bulgarian: "To my brother Delcho in Panagyurishte."</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Petar Pantaleev Karapetrov (1845 - 1903) was a publicist, printer, and publisher as well as a lawyer and Bulgarian magistrate. He was a member of the Bulgarian Literary Society (renamed "Bulgarian Academy of Sciences" in 1911).</ab>
